I mean, this newest
podcast that I'm working on

00:33:11.400 --> 00:33:14.350
is with Mary Robinson, who's
the former president of Ireland.

00:33:14.350 --> 00:33:16.860
She's their first
female president.

00:33:16.860 --> 00:33:18.870
And she's 73 years old now.

00:33:18.870 --> 00:33:22.260
And so you can imagine what it
was like for her coming off.

00:33:22.260 --> 00:33:26.370
She was a human rights
lawyer first in like,

00:33:26.370 --> 00:33:28.680
I guess the '70s
in Ireland, which

00:33:28.680 --> 00:33:30.026
was a tough time for women.

00:33:30.026 --> 00:33:31.650
And she was like a
human rights lawyer.

00:33:31.650 --> 00:33:35.130
So anyway I asked
her about that,

00:33:35.130 --> 00:33:42.300
because I think it's like a real
phenomenon with younger women.

00:33:42.300 --> 00:33:44.760
Maybe men feel it too,
imposter syndrome.

00:33:44.760 --> 00:33:48.540
I hear it most from women,
but maybe men feel it too.

00:33:48.540 --> 00:33:50.380
And I asked her about it.

00:33:50.380 --> 00:33:52.070
And she was like,
I never had it.

00:33:52.070 --> 00:33:53.400
[LAUGHTER]

00:33:53.400 --> 00:33:54.465
She was so unhelpful.

00:33:54.465 --> 00:33:55.130
[LAUGHTER]

00:33:55.130 --> 00:33:59.622
Like I really thought that she'd
have some kind of like wise,

00:33:59.622 --> 00:34:01.080
and she was just
like I don't know.

00:34:01.080 --> 00:34:05.130
[LAUGHTER]

00:34:05.130 --> 00:34:08.989
And someone else that
I talked to about this,

00:34:08.989 --> 00:34:10.679
she's a black woman.

00:34:10.679 --> 00:34:13.320
And she was like, that
I don't have time for--

00:34:13.320 --> 00:34:16.199
she's like, everyone
does doubt me.

00:34:16.199 --> 00:34:20.610
Everyone in her, I guess
she means not black people,

00:34:20.610 --> 00:34:24.850
does doubt her and she does have
to prove herself all the time.

00:34:24.850 --> 00:34:27.330
So if she also doubts herself--

00:34:27.330 --> 00:34:29.830
so that made me think this
is just one black woman.

00:34:29.830 --> 00:34:32.010
I don't know if that's--

00:34:32.010 --> 00:34:34.739
but that made me
think like I wonder

00:34:34.739 --> 00:34:39.670
if it's a bit of making a
problem where there isn't one.

00:34:42.340 --> 00:34:44.090
But I feel it.

00:34:44.090 --> 00:34:45.880
It's a real-- and I
know like feelings

00:34:45.880 --> 00:34:47.380
aren't facts, but whatever.

00:34:47.380 --> 00:34:48.985
I do still feel it a bit myself.

00:34:48.985 --> 00:34:50.020
KELLY: Yeah.

00:34:50.020 --> 00:34:53.260
MAEVE HIGGINS: And I feel like
what do I think I'm doing here,

00:34:53.260 --> 00:34:55.330
or if I'm doing like
a high-status thing

00:34:55.330 --> 00:34:59.620
or whatever, I'm like, me?

00:34:59.620 --> 00:35:05.820
I think it's helpful to
remind yourself of past.

00:35:05.820 --> 00:35:07.900
Like using logic helps me.

00:35:07.900 --> 00:35:10.540
Like I can say to myself,
but you did this other thing

00:35:10.540 --> 00:35:12.790
like two weeks ago, and
that was on the same level

00:35:12.790 --> 00:35:13.750
and you did fine.

00:35:13.750 --> 00:35:18.670
So like using logic to say
like, I wasn't cut out then.

00:35:18.670 --> 00:35:20.440
Nobody kicked me out then.

00:35:20.440 --> 00:35:22.610
So I can do this again.

00:35:22.610 --> 00:35:26.159
And then I use that for a lot
of things to trick my brain.

00:35:26.159 --> 00:35:27.700
Like I often think,
oh, I'm not going

00:35:27.700 --> 00:35:29.320
to be able to write this piece.

00:35:29.320 --> 00:35:32.040
Like it's too hard, or it's
too long, or it's whatever.

00:35:32.040 --> 00:35:32.867
I don't have time.

00:35:32.867 --> 00:35:34.450
But then I think,
but you thought that

00:35:34.450 --> 00:35:35.420
before but you did it.

00:35:35.420 --> 00:35:38.504
So just using evidence
from your past.

00:35:38.504 --> 00:35:39.420
KELLY: That's amazing.

00:35:39.420 --> 00:35:42.190
I mean, we're a very
databased company.

00:35:42.190 --> 00:35:43.610
It should resonate for us.

00:35:43.610 --> 00:35:44.443
MAEVE HIGGINS: Yeah?

00:35:44.443 --> 00:35:45.580
KELLY: Yeah.

